# Orchestrator — AdvertEyes run

## Identity
- slug: `adverteyes`
- registry id: **13** (next sequential; highest existing = 12)
- run dir: `upwork-runs/adverteyes/`
- demo path: `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/adverteyes/`
- live demo: `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/adverteyes/`
- work-sample route: `/work-samples/adverteyes`

## What this is
Fictional client **AdvertEyes** = a billboard + truckside (wrapped trucks) + digital
(DOOH screen) out-of-home advertising company. The posting asks for a custom
**internal business platform**: admin dashboard, user mgmt, RBAC, REST APIs,
DB-driven workflows, third-party API integration, responsive React frontend.
Not a SaaS — an internal ops tool for the OOH ad company's teams.

Michael's directive: build a genuinely useful internal web app for this OOH
company. Backend in **Node + TypeScript**, frontend in **React + TypeScript**,
clean + scalable. Integrate at least one **free API** (weather is the obvious
fit; see below for a stronger angle).

## Feature richness: 10/10
Build a full, production-quality app with several real working features. This is
a `full` build (not a prototype). Per CLAUDE.md caps still apply: 1 hero + at
most 2 supporting features, demo touches ~12 files. At richness 10 interpret
"feature" generously — the hero can be a multi-view module — but keep scope
fenced and shippable.

## Domain model (give intake/planner a head start)
The natural internal platform for an OOH ad company is an **inventory + campaign
operations dashboard**. Core entities:
- **Inventory units**: billboards (static/digital), truck-side wraps (mobile),
  DOOH screens. Each has location (lat/lng or route), size, type, availability,
  base rate.
- **Clients / advertisers** and their **campaigns** (flights with start/end,
  budget, assigned inventory units, creative).
- **Bookings** linking campaigns to inventory over date ranges (avoid
  double-booking).
- **Users + roles**: Admin, Sales, Ops/Installer, Client-viewer — RBAC gates
  what each sees/does.

## Why weather is a genuinely useful (not gimmick) integration here
For OOH advertising, **weather drives real decisions**: digital billboard
dayparting/creative swaps, install scheduling for truck wraps and static
billboards (no vinyl install in rain/high wind), and impression estimates.
Recommended free API: **Open-Meteo** (`api.open-meteo.com`) — no API key,
generous free tier, current + forecast by lat/lng. Use it to show a
weather/install-risk panel per billboard location and flag campaigns/installs at
risk. This satisfies "integrate a free API" while being domain-credible.
(Backup if a key is acceptable: OpenWeatherMap, but Open-Meteo's no-key model is
cleaner for a demo.)

## Suggested hero + supporting (planner decides finally)
- **Hero**: Campaign Operations Dashboard — inventory map/table, campaign
  bookings with conflict detection, KPI tiles, filterable reports/tables, RBAC
  views. This is the "admin dashboard + user mgmt + DB-driven workflows" core.
- **Supporting 1**: Weather/install-risk integration (Open-Meteo) per location.
- **Supporting 2**: User & role management (RBAC) with protected routes + a
  seeded demo login per role.

## Build/stack guidance
- Frontend: **React + TypeScript + Vite**, `base: '/demos/adverteyes/'`, build,
  copy `dist/*` into `public/demos/adverteyes/`. Keep demo source under
  `upwork-runs/adverteyes/demo-src/`. (Bundler warranted: TS + multi-view +
  RBAC + map/charts.)
- Backend: posting wants Node/TS/Express. **Decision point for planner+CEO**:
  CLAUDE.md's native backend path is a Flask blueprint OR a Surface-hosted
  Node/Express service bridged through Flask. Since Michael explicitly asked for
  a **Node/TypeScript backend**, the credible path is the **Surface runner**:
  build a Node+Express+TS service, register it as a service, bridge it via
  `<feature>_blueprint.py` at `api.michaelwegter.com/adverteyes/...`. Seed demo
  DB (SQLite/Postgres-lite or JSON store) with inventory/campaigns/users.
  - Lower-risk fallback if Surface Node build proves flaky within budget:
    front-load realistic seeded data in-frontend + Open-Meteo called directly
    from the browser, and present the Node/TS service as the documented
    architecture. Prefer the real Node service if achievable (matches the brief
    and Michael's ask). Record which path in `plan.md` per the prototype-vs-full
    rule.

## Design direction (bespoke — NOT michaelwegter.com's look)
OOH advertising is bold, visual, out-of-home. Aim for a confident operations-tool
aesthetic: strong but professional, high-contrast, map-forward. Researcher to
pull real OOH-industry/competitor cues (Lamar, Clear Channel Outdoor, OUTFRONT);
planner to set exact palette/typography/mood. Do not reuse the portfolio's dark
gallery theme or mustard/cyan.

## Pipeline (recommended layout)
with-ceo + with-deploy: intake -> planner -> CEO -> researcher -> demo-builder ->
deploy -> deploy-test -> media-capture -> proposal-writer -> evaluator
(-> prompt-optimizer). Backend means deploy pushes both repos; deploy-test hits
the live bridged endpoint.

## Required "to apply" answers (proposal-writer must cover all)
Posting requires the application to include: (1) experience w/ custom web apps,
(2) examples of admin dashboards/internal tools built, (3) strongest FE+BE
stack, (4) API-integration experience, (5) availability this week. US-only
freelancers; expert/hourly; <30 hrs/wk; 1-3 months. Cover letter must hit each
explicitly.

